{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1784143059,"nonce":"cyTa3Pnov+Bqhin/GjBnVjoNOJM=","kind":"spec","title":"Unified interactive viewer — converge kref show + kref todo cockpit (design)"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1784143059,"nonce":"B8ksXYMzqriNudxIrcdAD+GlUmA=","body":"# Unified interactive viewer — converge kref show + kref todo cockpit (design)\n\nStatus: design approved 2026-07-15 (Trevor). Capstone of the todo-cockpit\nusability arc: the unified-reader work already merged the READING side of\n`kref show` and `kref todo` (shared `internal/tui.ScrollView`, `internal/outline`\nfold, shared search/nav); this converges the WRITING side too, so there is one\ninteractive entry viewer instead of two overlapping models.\n\n## Problem\n\nThe comment WRITER (reply/edit/delete/resolve, textarea modal) lives only in the\n`kref todo` cockpit. A reader instinctively tries to add a comment from\n`kref show` and cannot. Meanwhile `pager.go` (the show reader, ~596 lines) and\n`cockpit_tui.go` (the cockpit, ~983 lines) are two interactive models that\nalready overlap heavily on reading. Converge them so comment-writing is generic\nacross the board and the reader duplication is retired.\n\n## Decisions (Trevor, 2026-07-15)\n\n1. CONVERGE: one interactive entry viewer. `kref show \u003cid\u003e` on a TTY IS that\n   viewer (read + fold + search + nav AND write/reply/edit/delete/resolve\n   comments on any entry). `kref todo` = the same viewer with the todo\n   header/deltas and Done-collapse injected. `pager.go` is retired.\n2. DEFAULT INTERACTIVE: every `kref show` on a TTY is the interactive viewer; the\n   write keys are inert until the cursor is on a comment, so a pure reader is\n   unaffected. Static output on a pipe / `--plain` / `--no-pager` is unchanged\n   (the same gate the cockpit already uses).\n\n## Target architecture\n\nOne viewer model (the current `cockpitModel`, generalized and renamed off \"todo\")\ncomposed of:\n\n- Shared reading: `internal/tui.ScrollView` + `internal/outline` fold + shared\n  search/nav (already in place from the unified-reader arc).\n- Generic writer: the cockpit's `commentWriter` (a subset of `*store.Store`:\n  AddComment/ResolveComment/EditComment/DeleteComment) + the textarea modal +\n  r/e/d/x + reload closure. Operates on plain `[]entry.Comment`, so it is already\n  entry-agnostic.\n- Content-type-aware body render: adopt the pager's glamour/chroma rendering so\n  the viewer renders any entry's body (markdown, code, etc.), not just todo\n  markdown.\n- Pluggable header provider: `kref todo` supplies the awaiting/delta/version\n  header + `todo.Sections`/Done-collapse; `kref show` supplies the entry identity\n  + the existing `--header` / `e`-expand extended header. The viewer core is\n  header-agnostic.\n\nThe merge is three seams: WRITER (lift into the shared viewer), BODY RENDER\n(adopt the pager's content-type render), HEADER (make it a pluggable provider).\n\n## Feature preservation (nothing lost)\n\n- From `kref show`: content-type render, `e`-expand-header, `?` hotkey popup,\n  no-clear-screen on exit, layered `esc` dismiss, `ctrl+r` reload.\n- From `kref todo`: the comment writer (reply/edit/delete/resolve, `$EDITOR`\n  escape), the todo header + awaiting/changed/to-review deltas, Done-collapse,\n  colour toggle, `↓N` footer, the dual-grammar nav.\n\n## Decomposition (own-cycle phases, each spec -\u003e plan -\u003e build)\n\n- 1 — Extract the generic viewer out of the cockpit: rename off `cockpitModel`,\n  push the todo-specific header + sections behind a small header-provider\n  interface. The todo cockpit keeps working with no behaviour change; this is a\n  pure structural extraction that isolates the todo coupling.\n- 2 — Port the pager's content-type body rendering + show-only features\n  (`e`-expand, `?` popup, no-clear, layered `esc`) into the generic viewer.\n- 3 — Point `kref show` (TTY) at the generic viewer with the comment writer\n  enabled and the show header provider; retire `pager.go`. Static path unchanged.\n- 4 — Point `kref todo` at the generic viewer via the todo header provider;\n  converge and de-duplicate the show/cockpit test suites.\n\n## Risks / notes\n\n- Big test surface: both the show pager suite and the cockpit suite exercise the\n  merged model; phase 4 reconciles them. Interactive FEEL needs a real-TTY pass\n  (model tests assert behaviour, not feel).\n- Behaviour change: `kref show` on a TTY becomes an interactive writer by default\n  (intended, per decision 2). Document it and the inert-until-on-a-comment rule.\n- Synergy with the quarantine-review arc (`kref show 4cb93aef7611`): its review\n  threads are ordinary comments, so a generic writer means a reviewer discusses a\n  quarantine review right from `kref show \u003ctarget\u003e`.\n\n## Open questions (resolve in the phase specs)\n\n- Where the generic viewer lives: stay in `cmd/kref` (it is the CLI's interactive\n  layer, uses store/render/outline/todo) vs move core to `internal/tui`. Lean:\n  keep in `cmd/kref`, only ScrollView-level primitives stay in `internal/tui`.\n- The header-provider interface shape (what the viewer asks a provider for:\n  sticky header lines, section model, delta signals).\n- Whether phase 3 and 4 can land together or must be sequenced (both touch the\n  entry point wiring).\n"},{"type":9,"timestamp":1784143059,"nonce":"F/e7AD+6fldZSQdpbM2wlq81GoE=","label":"area:design"},{"type":11,"timestamp":1784143059,"nonce":"sjdjPIcUYc1vVONwpkL1h6GT2Xw=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"","trigger":"create"},{"type":5,"timestamp":1784143070,"nonce":"VO0mtNPGC1IlltlVGGTrE1Unr1M=","to":"81be409e4ef81864f5b3ca115375975cc3adc9ae256c44279148778c9506085e","link_type":"relates"},{"type":11,"timestamp":1784224331,"nonce":"wOSxXF9MorND+/RPGTxEYoQEctQ=","actor":"Trevor Vaughan","actor_kind":"human","source_path":"","trigger":"retier"}]}